  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">A high school principal collects some data about students at his school. He uses his student information system to find the grade point average (GPA) of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$10$</span> random students. The GPAs are listed below: </div><div class=\"paragraph\"><div class=\"tex2jax_process\">$$3.2, 3.7, 4.0, 2.5, 3.1, 3.5, 3.8, 3.0, 2.7, 2.5$$</div></div><div class=\"paragraph\">This gives the principal an average GPA of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$3.2$</span> on a <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$4$</span> point scale. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">Can the principal confidently say that the average GPA of his high school is <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$3.2$</span>?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
